This paper deals with the problem of multi-robot search and rendezvous, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and theoretical analysis (cs.DS) to solve the problem. The use of symmetric strategies (cs.AI) and the consideration of both synchronous and asynchronous cases (cs.SY) further support these categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of mathematical analysis and optimization (cs.MA) to determine the competitive ratios of the proposed algorithms.
